sentences.english: Malekula island Vanuatu. His face is covered with ash for the dance.

sentences.english: The Republic of Vanuatu is located near the east coast of Australia.

sentences.english: We are in the Yakel Village on the South Pacific island chain of Vanuatu.

sentences.english: The Vanuatu people have always viewed China as their best friend.
sentences.chinese: 瓦努阿圖人民始終把中國視爲他們最好的朋友。

sentences.english: Vanuatu cherished its friendship with China and would continue to adhere to the one-China policy, Natapei said, hoping that China would continue to help and cooperate with his country.
sentences.chinese: 瓦努阿圖將繼續堅定地奉行一箇中國政策。

sentences.english: Vanuatu is an island country there with a population of about 267,000 people.
sentences.chinese: 瓦努阿圖是一個島嶼國家，人口有267000人。

sentences.english: Vanuatu was one of the few places that was colonised jointly by two countries.
sentences.chinese: 瓦努阿圖是少數幾個由兩個國家共同殖民的國家之一。

sentences.english: Vanuatu strongly promotes private sector led growth.
sentences.chinese: 瓦努阿圖大力促進私營經濟的增長。
